---
/**
 * About Page
 *
 * Preserves the original DigiHoof about page design exactly.
 */

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="DigiHoof was created to solve the communication gap between veterinarians and farriers when it comes to hoof radiograph findings. Learn about our mission and approach."
>

<section class="split-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>About DigiHoof</h1>

    <p>
      DigiHoof was created to address a persistent challenge in equine practice:
      the communication gap between veterinarians and farriers
      when it comes to hoof radiograph findings.
      Radiographs contain critical information about hoof balance and pathology,
      but that information is only useful when both professionals can see it clearly.
    </p>

    <p>
      The platform generates standardized, shareable hoof radiograph reports
      with consistent overlays and measurements —
      giving veterinarians and farriers a common visual language
      for discussing hoof health and making trim or shoeing decisions together.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="split-section alt">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Built for Real-World Equine Practice</h2>

    <p>
      DigiHoof reflects the operational realities of busy equine clinics.
      Report generation is fast enough to fit into high-volume imaging days,
      because when creating reports is quick, it's far more likely to happen consistently.
    </p>

    <p>
      Every design decision focuses on practical usability:
      rapid landmark placement, automated measurements,
      consistent layouts across visits,
      and mobile-friendly sharing that farriers can access without technical barriers.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="split-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>AI-Assisted, Veterinarian-Led</h2>

    <p>
      DigiHoof uses machine learning to assist with landmark detection
      and measurement standardization on hoof radiographs.
      This helps normalize how reports are generated across cases
      while preserving the veterinarian's clinical judgment and final interpretation.
    </p>

    <p>
      The goal is not to replace expertise
      but to make professional-quality reporting realistic
      within the time constraints of everyday practice.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="split-section alt">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Better Collaboration for the Horse's Benefit</h2>

    <p>
      When veterinarians and farriers work from the same clear data,
      the horse benefits.
      DigiHoof ensures that hoof balance, alignment, and change over time
      are communicated consistently —
      supporting better trimming, shoeing, and management decisions.
    </p>

    <p>
      Longitudinal tracking with standardized reports
      makes real comparison possible across visits,
      turning hoof radiography into a collaborative, ongoing conversation
      rather than a static snapshot.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="split-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Operated by DigiScan LLC</h2>

    <p>
      DigiHoof is operated by DigiScan LLC,
      a United States–based company focused on developing
      modern equine imaging and reporting tools.
    </p>

    <p>
      Built by an equine veterinarian who works directly with farriers,
      DigiHoof is grounded in real-world practice — not theory.
      The mission is to deliver professional reporting tools
      that actually get used because they fit into how practices work.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
